non_residential_details.development_type: Change of Use with Extension(s) over 999sqm

description: Non-material amendment to planning application 2015/0877 dated 04/12/2015 (as amended by 2016/2079) in order to undertake the following amendments:  - Increase in height of north tower by 0.5m and south tower by 2.0m. Also includes minor changes to balustrade heights  - Other changes to massing including a slight amendment to the building geometry and the revised massing of Level 7 and Level 10 - Revisions to residential openable windows - Façade amendments associated with residential layout changes and loss of office core - Removal of two floors of below ground space (lower ground floor and one basement level) and rationalisation of space at basement levels - Plant rationalisation - Changes to south tower core and office core, and removal of office stair core facing the courtyard - Loss of car stacker and loss of 22 car parking spaces  - Amendments to cycle parking and cycle entrance - Amendment to layout of servicing arrangement - Mezzanine bridge link omitted  - Lightwell in courtyard omitted - Amendment to residential layouts - Amendment to residential mix and numbers (reduction from 247 to 246) - Amendment to wording of Condition 35 (number of units) - Change of use of ground floor space at 54 Wilson Street from flexible B1/A1/A3 to B1 - Extension to rear of 54 Wilson Street to provide 237sqm of additional B1 floorspace at lower and ground floor level - Amendment to development description to remove reference to flexible use at ground floor within 54 Wilson Street, flexible office/retail floorspace at lower ground level within east building (Class B1/A1/A3/A4), office use (Class B1) at lower ground within east building and car parking.  The application includes the submission of an EIA Statement of Conformity pursuant to the Town and Country Planning (Environmental Impact Assessment) Regulations 2011.
